Thanks to Lazar Lyusternik and at least one other person from chat who I forgot to note. Thanks for putting up with my constant begging for draft reviews!

Anyone searching for answers to inconsistencies, errors or anything else out of the ordinary should try rereading the article, and then clicking the collapsible.

+commentary

-block


First off, the SERS was created by this post. When I saw it, I knew it was SCP fuel, and it fit here perfectly.

As for what's going on, well, there's like 85% chaff in this article, for a good reason: the Foundation has no idea what's going on while being completely assured that they have the situation under control. Put simply, every time they take a Hume reading of the anomaly, it grows and goes active. If they stopped trying to actively contain it, it would do nothing could be considered Safe. I hope this comes through, I tried to leave a lot of bread crumbs for the reader. D:

This article has been published about three years too late.  is a problem to which a single solution can be applied, frankly, ridiculous, and I wanted to encapsulate that ridiculousness in an article.

So yeah, most of this is just stuff you'd expect to see in a somewhat lengthy SCP article  with a few nuggets of what's actually going on hidden within. This is one of my longer articles, and also, my first Keter. :V Thank you for reading.








